  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>A metric space is a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> together with a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0009.xml" addr="FA-0009" title="Distance Measure">distance measure</fr:link> (or metric) <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d]]></fr:tex> that defines a concept of distance between any two members of the set.</fr:p>
    <fr:p>The metric satisfies the following properties:</fr:p>
    <fr:ul><fr:li>Non-negativity: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x,y) \geq  0]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>Identity of indiscernibles: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x,y) = 0]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x = y]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>Symmetry: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x,y) = d(y,x)]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>Triangle inequality: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(x,z) \leq  d(x,y) + d(y,z)]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ul>
  </fr:mainmatter>
