            <fr:title text="Norm">Norm</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A norm on a vector space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> is a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||\cdot ||: V \rightarrow  \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> that assigns a non-negative real number to each vector in the space, satisfying the following axioms for all vectors <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u, v \in  V]]></fr:tex> and scalars <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex>:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li><fr:strong>Non-negativity:</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||v|| \geq  0]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||v|| = 0]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v = 0]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:strong>Absolute homogeneity:</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||av|| = |a| \cdot  ||v||]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:strong>Triangle inequality:</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||u + v|| \leq  ||u|| + ||v||]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ul>
            <fr:p>A norm generalizes the intuitive notion of length or magnitude to abstract vector spaces. It induces a metric <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(u,v) = ||u-v||]]></fr:tex> on the vector space, making it a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000G.xml" addr="FA-000G" title="Metric Space">metric space</fr:link>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Common examples of norms include:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li>The Euclidean norm on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}^n]]></fr:tex>: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||x||_2 = \sqrt {x_1^2 + x_2^2 + \cdots  + x_n^2}]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>The <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex>-norm on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}^n]]></fr:tex>: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||x||_p = \left ( |x_1|^p + |x_2|^p + \cdots  + |x_n|^p \right )^{1/p}]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p \geq  1]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>The maximum norm on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}^n]]></fr:tex>: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||x||_\infty  = \max \{|x_1|, |x_2|, \ldots , |x_n|\}]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>The <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000E.xml" addr="FA-000E" title="Sup norm">sup norm</fr:link> on function spaces: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||f||_\infty  = \sup _{x} |f(x)|]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>The <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L^p]]></fr:tex> norm on function spaces: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||f||_p = \left (\int  |f(x)|^p dx\right )^{1/p}]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p \geq  1]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ul>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
