            <fr:title text="Normed vector space">Normed vector space</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A normed vector space is a vector space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> equipped with a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0018.xml" addr="FA-0018" title="Norm">norm</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||\cdot ||: V \rightarrow  \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex>, which is a function that assigns a non-negative real number to each vector in the space, satisfying the following properties for all vectors <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u, v \in  V]]></fr:tex> and scalars <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex>:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li><fr:strong>Non-negativity:</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||v|| \geq  0]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||v|| = 0]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v = 0]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:strong>Absolute homogeneity:</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||av|| = |a| \cdot  ||v||]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:strong>Triangle inequality:</fr:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||u + v|| \leq  ||u|| + ||v||]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ul>
            <fr:p>A norm induces a metric <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[d(u,v) = ||u-v||]]></fr:tex> on the space, making it a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000G.xml" addr="FA-000G" title="Metric Space">metric space</fr:link>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Common examples of norms include:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li>The Euclidean norm on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}^n]]></fr:tex>: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||x||_2 = \sqrt {x_1^2 + x_2^2 + \cdots  + x_n^2}]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>The <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L^p]]></fr:tex> norms on function spaces: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||f||_p = \left (\int  |f(x)|^p dx\right )^{1/p}]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>The <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000E.xml" addr="FA-000E" title="Sup norm">sup norm</fr:link> on spaces of bounded functions: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||f||_\infty  = \sup _{x} |f(x)|]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ul>
            <fr:p>A <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000F.xml" addr="FA-000F" title="Banach Space">Banach space</fr:link> is a complete normed vector space.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
